362
00:16:43,931 --> 00:16:45,551
♪ He wants to understand

363
00:16:45,586 --> 00:16:47,068
♪ What makes it all so grand

364
00:16:47,103 --> 00:16:50,482
♪ On every Christmas Eve

365
00:16:50,517 --> 00:16:53,965
[upbeat Christmas music]

366
00:17:06,448 --> 00:17:07,965
Winslow didn't know it,

367
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:10,413
but everyone in the forest
had heard about his story

368
00:17:12,344 --> 00:17:13,620
and they were all wondering

369
00:17:13,655 --> 00:17:16,413
if Winslow would
really find his answer.

370
00:17:16,448 --> 00:17:20,724
Everyone was interested,
but some more than others.

371
00:17:20,758 --> 00:17:23,103
The wolf family was
also very interested

372
00:17:23,137 --> 00:17:24,379
in Winslow's journey.

373
00:17:24,413 --> 00:17:27,000
They had been following
him the whole time

374
00:17:27,034 --> 00:17:30,827
and soon now, they
would make their move.

375
00:17:30,862 --> 00:17:32,793
Winslow didn't even
know they were there

376
00:17:32,827 --> 00:17:35,103
as he looked around the valley.

377
00:17:35,137 --> 00:17:37,172
Meanwhile, while
he was on his way,

378
00:17:37,206 --> 00:17:40,551
Winslow ran into someone
else quite by accident.

379
00:17:40,586 --> 00:17:42,724
It was Larry the Mountain Linx.

380
00:17:42,758 --> 00:17:45,448
- [Winslow] Excuse me,
I'm sorry to interrupt,

381
00:17:45,482 --> 00:17:46,689
but I was just wondering

382
00:17:46,724 --> 00:17:49,517
if you could tell me
what Christmas is.

383
00:17:49,551 --> 00:17:50,724
- [Larry] Oh, hi Winslow.

384
00:17:50,758 --> 00:17:51,689
What are you doing up?

385
00:17:51,724 --> 00:17:52,931
- [Narrator] He was curious

386
00:17:52,965 --> 00:17:55,034
why a bear would be
up Christmas Eve.

387
00:17:55,068 --> 00:17:57,103
The little linx
was one of the most

388
00:17:57,137 --> 00:17:59,586
playful and happy
friends that Winslow had,

389
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:04,103
always running and climbing
and jumping every which way.

390
00:18:04,137 --> 00:18:07,344
He made Winslow tired
just to watch him.

391
00:18:07,379 --> 00:18:09,758
Sometimes he played with
his sister, Loretta.

392
00:18:09,793 --> 00:18:11,896
Sometimes he just ran
around by himself.

393
00:18:15,551 --> 00:18:17,482
Finally, he stopped
just long enough

394
00:18:17,517 --> 00:18:19,137
for Winslow to say something.

395
00:18:19,172 --> 00:18:21,379
- [Winslow] Do you
know what Christmas is?

396
00:18:21,413 --> 00:18:24,310
- [Larry] Sure, Christmas is
playing, plain and simple.

397
00:18:24,344 --> 00:18:27,206
- [Winslow] Christmas certainly
is different for everyone.

398
00:18:27,241 --> 00:18:28,586
- [Larry] Of course it is.

399
00:18:28,620 --> 00:18:30,310
It's the best time of the year.

400
00:18:30,344 --> 00:18:32,758
- [Narrator] Winslow realized
that every one of his friends

401
00:18:32,793 --> 00:18:36,931
had a very different idea
about Christmas, how confusing?

402
00:18:36,965 --> 00:18:38,379
He knew less now than he did

403
00:18:38,413 --> 00:18:40,275
when he was back in his cave.

404
00:18:40,310 --> 00:18:41,827
- [Larry] Aren't you gonna stay?

405
00:18:41,862 --> 00:18:45,275
- [Winslow] Can't, I think
I'll go ask Mother Cougar.

406
00:18:45,310 --> 00:18:48,068
She knows about everything
here in the forest.

407
00:18:48,103 --> 00:18:50,448
- [Larry] Winslow, you know
that the wolves are around,

408
00:18:50,482 --> 00:18:51,586
don't you?

409
00:18:51,620 --> 00:18:53,965
- [Winslow] Yes,
I've heard that.

410
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:56,413
- [Larry] Oh, everybody
says they're very hungry.

411
00:18:56,448 --> 00:18:58,068
The whole family
is running around

412
00:18:58,103 --> 00:19:00,000
looking for a big
Christmas dinner.

413
00:19:00,034 --> 00:19:02,000
- [Winslow] Thanks
for telling me.

414
00:19:02,034 --> 00:19:04,482
- [Larry] Oh, your very
welcome funny old bear.

415
00:19:04,517 --> 00:19:05,931
Merry Christmas.

416
00:19:11,068 --> 00:19:14,379
- [Narrator] Mother Cougar was
a very large mountain lion.

417
00:19:14,413 --> 00:19:15,862
She had lived in the forest

418
00:19:15,896 --> 00:19:19,000
longer than anyone could
remember, including Winslow.

419
00:19:19,034 --> 00:19:21,586
She knew everything.

420
00:19:21,620 --> 00:19:22,931
While Winslow looked for her,

421
00:19:22,965 --> 00:19:24,724
the wolves were getting closer.

422
00:19:24,758 --> 00:19:27,620
Now, Mother Cougar
liked to perch herself

423
00:19:27,655 --> 00:19:31,206
on the very highest peak so
that she could watch everything.

424
00:19:33,448 --> 00:19:34,655
But Winslow wasn't so sure

425
00:19:34,689 --> 00:19:36,448
that he wanted to
be up this high.

426
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:40,310
- [Winslow] Whoa, I
better be careful.

427
00:19:40,344 --> 00:19:45,137
I could fall a very long
way, that's real steep.

428
00:19:45,172 --> 00:19:47,655
Maybe I'll just go
around the easy path

429
00:19:47,689 --> 00:19:49,344
and talk to Mother Cougar.

430
00:19:53,448 --> 00:19:54,482
- [Mother] Winslow the
Bear, I thought it was you.

431
00:19:55,862 --> 00:19:57,482
What are you doing way up here?

432
00:19:58,827 --> 00:20:00,448
- [Winslow] Climbing.

433
00:20:00,482 --> 00:20:03,206
I'm just trying to get up
there to talk with you.

434
00:20:03,241 --> 00:20:06,827
- [Mother] And what on earth
are you doing up in the winter?

435
00:20:06,862 --> 00:20:09,034
- [Winslow] There's
something I need to ask you.

436
00:20:09,068 --> 00:20:11,034
- [Mother] You are
supposed to be sleeping,

437
00:20:11,068 --> 00:20:13,034
bears hibernate in the winter.

438
00:20:13,068 --> 00:20:16,206
- [Winslow] Yes, I know, but
I need to ask you something

439
00:20:16,241 --> 00:20:19,551
because you're the wisest
animal in the forest.

440
00:20:19,586 --> 00:20:20,931
What's Christmas?

441
00:20:20,965 --> 00:20:23,034
- [Mother] You got up
in the middle of winter

442
00:20:23,068 --> 00:20:25,206
to ask me that?

443
00:20:25,241 --> 00:20:26,413
- [Winslow] Yes I did.

444
00:20:26,448 --> 00:20:27,655
Do you know?

445
00:20:27,689 --> 00:20:28,586
- [Mother] Well,
of course I know.

446
00:20:28,620 --> 00:20:30,275
Christmas is singing.

447
00:20:30,310 --> 00:20:31,862
The humans call it caroling.

448
00:20:31,896 --> 00:20:35,241
I call it noise, but
that's what it is, singing.

449
00:20:35,275 --> 00:20:36,482
- [Winslow] Singing?

450
00:20:36,517 --> 00:20:38,344
- [Mother] Not worth
getting up for, was it?

451
00:20:38,379 --> 00:20:39,551
Here, I'll show you.

452
00:20:40,517 --> 00:20:43,551
♪ Winslow the Christmas bear

453
00:20:43,586 --> 00:20:45,689
♪ Silly old bear

454
00:20:45,724 --> 00:20:47,241
- [Winslow] Like this?

455
00:20:47,275 --> 00:20:50,344
- [Narrator] Winslow tried to
sing, but he wasn't very good.

456
00:20:50,379 --> 00:20:51,793
- [Mother] You
call that singing?

457
00:20:51,827 --> 00:20:53,448
You sing like a bear.

458
00:20:55,275 --> 00:20:57,034
- [Narrator] Winslow
knew he sang like a bear.

459
00:20:57,068 --> 00:20:58,379
He kinda liked it.

460
00:20:59,620 --> 00:21:01,344
- [Mother] And Winslow,
one more thing.

461
00:21:01,379 --> 00:21:04,034
- [Winslow] I already
know, the wolves are out.

462
00:21:04,068 --> 00:21:06,310
- [Mother] Correct and
they're coming this way.

463
00:21:06,344 --> 00:21:09,275
If I were you, I wouldn't
be here when they arrive.

464
00:21:09,310 --> 00:21:11,137
- [Winslow] That's
a very good idea.

465
00:21:11,172 --> 00:21:13,758
I'm going now, goodbye.

466
00:21:13,793 --> 00:21:15,241
- [Narrator] And Winslow
left the mountain top.

467
00:21:15,275 --> 00:21:18,413
Mother Cougar stood up on
the rock and watched him go,

468
00:21:18,448 --> 00:21:21,413
she was worried about
the funny old bear.

469
00:21:23,068 --> 00:21:24,758
- [Mother] Time for me to go to.

470
00:21:24,793 --> 00:21:27,379
Can't leave the children
too long, you know?

471
00:21:27,413 --> 00:21:28,931
- [Narrator] As she left,

472
00:21:28,965 --> 00:21:31,206
the father of the wolf family,
Willard, watched her run off.

473
00:21:33,965 --> 00:21:35,275
Then he followed.

474
00:21:38,724 --> 00:21:40,689
Chrissy was afraid for Winslow.

475
00:21:40,724 --> 00:21:44,517
She scrunched up her pillow
so it was just right.

476
00:21:46,310 --> 00:21:47,655
Then she kept on reading.

477
00:21:50,206 --> 00:21:52,344
Now, after Winslow
left the mountain top,

478
00:21:52,379 --> 00:21:53,896
he went into the valley thicket

479
00:21:53,931 --> 00:21:56,724
to see who else he could find
to talk to about Christmas.

480
00:21:57,827 --> 00:21:58,862
Wait a minute.

481
00:21:58,896 --> 00:22:00,310
Someone was in the thicket.

482
00:22:01,517 --> 00:22:04,103
Why it's Kenneth, the
crafty little coyote.

483
00:22:06,413 --> 00:22:07,689
- [Winslow] I'll just say hello.

484
00:22:07,724 --> 00:22:10,586
Kenneth, it's me, Winslow.

485
00:22:10,620 --> 00:22:12,068
- [Narrator] But Kenneth
didn't hear Winslow

486
00:22:12,103 --> 00:22:16,965
and off he went every which
way, here, there, everywhere.

487
00:22:17,689 --> 00:22:18,172
- [Winslow] Hello?

488
00:22:18,206 --> 00:22:19,068
It's me.

489
00:22:23,896 --> 00:22:25,068
Kenneth, where are you?

490
00:22:25,103 --> 00:22:27,310
I can't go very fast, Kenneth.

491
00:22:27,344 --> 00:22:28,965
Could you slow down?

492
00:22:30,379 --> 00:22:32,275
- [Kenneth] Hey Winslow,
you wanna play tag?

493
00:22:32,310 --> 00:22:35,275
- [Winslow] Wait Kenneth,
I didn't come to play tag.

494
00:22:35,310 --> 00:22:37,655
I wanted to ask you something.

495
00:22:37,689 --> 00:22:40,448
- [Kenneth] I'm over
here buddy, come on.

496
00:22:40,482 --> 00:22:41,689
- [Winslow] Wait a minute.

497
00:22:41,724 --> 00:22:42,965
Where are you?

498
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:44,137
Kenneth?

499
00:22:44,172 --> 00:22:46,034
- [Kenneth] This way,
try and catch me.

500
00:22:46,068 --> 00:22:48,655
- [Winslow] But I can't
go as fast as you.

501
00:22:48,689 --> 00:22:49,689
Kenneth?

502
00:22:50,896 --> 00:22:53,724
Kenneth, you're a
lot faster than me.

503
00:22:54,931 --> 00:22:57,103
- [Kenneth] Run again
Winslow, over here.

504
00:22:57,137 --> 00:22:58,793
- [Winslow] Please slow down.

505
00:23:00,551 --> 00:23:03,413
Kenneth, hello?

506
00:23:03,448 --> 00:23:04,448
Boy, he's sure fast.

507
00:23:05,448 --> 00:23:06,758
- [Narrator] Poor Winslow,

508
00:23:06,793 --> 00:23:08,655
every time he got
close to the coyote,

509
00:23:08,689 --> 00:23:11,379
Kenneth would just zip
off in another direction.

510
00:23:11,413 --> 00:23:14,310
He just couldn't get that
coyote to stop for a minute.

511
00:23:14,344 --> 00:23:17,517
Winslow went on searching
for the longest time,

512
00:23:17,551 --> 00:23:19,068
but he didn't find Kenneth.

513
00:23:32,344 --> 00:23:35,965
Just then, Winslow heard
the strangest sound.

514
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:38,655
[poking sounds]

515
00:23:44,068 --> 00:23:46,724
- [Porky] Oh no, don't eat
me, I don't taste good.

516
00:23:46,758 --> 00:23:47,724
Please don't eat me.

517
00:23:47,758 --> 00:23:49,172
You wouldn't like me.

518
00:23:49,206 --> 00:23:52,896
I'm all stringy and
tough and icky tasting.

519
00:23:52,931 --> 00:23:54,965
Get away, leave me alone!

520
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:56,206
Please let me go.

521
00:23:56,241 --> 00:23:58,000
- [Winslow] I'm not
going to eat you,

522
00:23:58,034 --> 00:24:00,000
slow down, it's okay.

523
00:24:00,034 --> 00:24:01,275
- [Porky] You wouldn't like me.

524
00:24:01,310 --> 00:24:04,172
Porcupines are real
bad nutritionally.

525
00:24:04,206 --> 00:24:05,862
I can see it in your eyes,

526
00:24:05,896 --> 00:24:07,758
you're gonna, you're
gonna gobble me down

527
00:24:07,793 --> 00:24:10,068
and spit out the needles.

528
00:24:10,103 --> 00:24:12,655
- [Winslow] I'm really not
going to eat you, Porky.

529
00:24:12,689 --> 00:24:15,068
I just wanted to
ask you a question.

530
00:24:15,103 --> 00:24:16,586
- [Winslow] Oh,
it's you Winslow.

531
00:24:16,620 --> 00:24:18,206
Oh man, am I glad it's you.

532
00:24:18,241 --> 00:24:20,620
I thought you were
one of the wolves,

533
00:24:20,655 --> 00:24:22,862
they'd make a
sandwich out of me.

534
00:24:22,896 --> 00:24:24,896
I'm so glad it's you instead.

535
00:24:24,931 --> 00:24:27,724
Don't ever sneak up on me again.

536
00:24:27,758 --> 00:24:29,172
You almost gave
me a heart attack,

537
00:24:29,206 --> 00:24:31,137
you fur covered bee bee brain.

538
00:24:31,172 --> 00:24:32,482
- [Winslow] I'm sorry.

539
00:24:32,517 --> 00:24:34,896
- [Narrator] Said
Winslow, and he was.

540
00:24:34,931 --> 00:24:37,586
Winslow decided maybe
he'd better not bother

541
00:24:37,620 --> 00:24:39,931
the frightened little
porcupine anymore.

542
00:24:39,965 --> 00:24:41,965
He'd just go ask someone else

543
00:24:43,655 --> 00:24:45,482
and that's exactly what he did.

544
00:24:50,862 --> 00:24:53,689
Winslow trudged down through
the snow covered mountains.

545
00:24:56,068 --> 00:24:57,241
While Winslow was asking

546
00:24:57,275 --> 00:24:59,034
all his animal friends
about Christmas,

547
00:24:59,068 --> 00:25:01,344
the day was passing quickly.

548
00:25:01,379 --> 00:25:03,758
Winslow was running
out of daylight.

549
00:25:03,793 --> 00:25:05,206
He had to hurry on his journey

550
00:25:05,241 --> 00:25:07,551
if he was going to
find out in time.

551
00:25:07,586 --> 00:25:11,068
He only had a few hours left
and then it would be night

552
00:25:12,344 --> 00:25:13,793
and then it would
be Christmas day

553
00:25:13,827 --> 00:25:17,000
and too late for anyone to tell
him, so he kept pushing on.

554
00:25:18,172 --> 00:25:19,586
He could see Eddie
the Great Eagle

555
00:25:19,620 --> 00:25:22,344
soaring high up in
the afternoon sky.

556
00:25:22,379 --> 00:25:24,344
Winslow was still
hoping that someone

557
00:25:24,379 --> 00:25:26,517
would have the answer
to his question

558
00:25:26,551 --> 00:25:30,551
before the day was over, then
something caught his ear.

559
00:25:31,827 --> 00:25:34,241
It was Sylvia,
the dancing skunk.

560
00:25:35,344 --> 00:25:37,517
She was very famous
in the forest.

561
00:25:37,551 --> 00:25:39,172
She danced very
well for a skunk.

562
00:25:41,655 --> 00:25:44,862
- [Winslow] Sylvia, does
Christmas mean dancing?

563
00:25:44,896 --> 00:25:48,241
- [Sylvia] No, Christmas is
about things that smell good.

564
00:25:48,275 --> 00:25:50,551
[laughter]

565
00:25:51,724 --> 00:25:55,034
What are you laughing
about banana nose?

566
00:25:56,413 --> 00:25:59,137
- [Winslow] A skunk that
likes things that smell good.

567
00:25:59,172 --> 00:26:03,482
- [Sylvia] Hey no neck,
you think that's funny?

568
00:26:03,517 --> 00:26:07,103
- [Winslow] I'm sorry, but
skunks don't smell good,

569
00:26:07,137 --> 00:26:08,620
they smell yucky.

570
00:26:10,413 --> 00:26:11,758
- [Sylvia] What you
know bear brain?

571
00:26:11,793 --> 00:26:14,586
You smell like an old fur coat.

572
00:26:14,620 --> 00:26:15,517
I'm outta here.

573
00:26:15,551 --> 00:26:17,896
Three, two, one, blast off.

574
00:26:19,482 --> 00:26:22,551
- [Winslow] Gosh, she's
real fast for a skunk.

575
00:26:22,586 --> 00:26:25,034
I guess I shouldn't
have laughed at her.

576
00:26:25,068 --> 00:26:28,517
I didn't even get to
ask her about Christmas.

577
00:26:28,551 --> 00:26:30,103
- [Narrator] Oh Winslow.

578
00:26:30,137 --> 00:26:32,655
It seemed he'd never
find out about Christmas.

579
00:26:35,862 --> 00:26:38,724
When suddenly he saw that
the entire wolf family

580
00:26:38,758 --> 00:26:40,551
was on the other
side of the valley.

581
00:26:41,724 --> 00:26:43,862
Oh, he was so scared,
he tried to climb a tree

582
00:26:43,896 --> 00:26:45,620
but it was too little.

583
00:26:45,655 --> 00:26:49,517
He tried to dig a hole, but
that didn't work either.

584
00:26:50,586 --> 00:26:53,000
The tree again, running
up the mountain,

585
00:26:56,482 --> 00:26:57,275
digging,

586
00:26:59,931 --> 00:27:01,586
nothing worked for Winslow.

587
00:27:04,689 --> 00:27:06,586
And they were on
their way toward him.

588
00:27:08,103 --> 00:27:11,241
No, no, no, he had to go!

589
00:27:11,275 --> 00:27:12,655
Here they come!

590
00:27:12,689 --> 00:27:15,206
- [Winslow] Oh no,
oh no, oh no, no.

591
00:27:16,655 --> 00:27:18,034
Wait, where did they go?

592
00:27:18,068 --> 00:27:20,655
I guess they weren't as
close as I thought they were.

593
00:27:22,862 --> 00:27:24,724
I better get out of here quick.

594
00:27:26,413 --> 00:27:28,482
- [Narrator] Winslow ran
to climb a bigger pine tree

595
00:27:28,517 --> 00:27:31,241
when he saw Bob the Bobcat.

596
00:27:31,275 --> 00:27:33,655
- [Winslow] Bob, can
I come up with you?

597
00:27:33,689 --> 00:27:35,310
- [Bob] What, are you crazy?

598
00:27:35,344 --> 00:27:37,482
There's no room for you up here.

599
00:27:37,517 --> 00:27:39,206
- [Winslow] I can't
stay down here.

600
00:27:39,241 --> 00:27:40,482
- [Bob] Winslow,
I'm telling you,

601
00:27:40,517 --> 00:27:42,413
you're too big for
this little tree.

602
00:27:42,448 --> 00:27:44,689
- [Winslow] Please, Bob.

603
00:27:44,724 --> 00:27:46,758
You won't even notice me.

604
00:27:50,172 --> 00:27:53,655
I'm sorry to intrude,
but I have to come up.

605
00:27:53,689 --> 00:27:55,172
- [Bob] Hey Winslow, you're
bigger than the whole tree.

606
00:27:55,206 --> 00:27:56,931
There ain't no room.

607
00:27:56,965 --> 00:27:58,344
Go find your own tree.

608
00:27:58,379 --> 00:27:59,931
Giant Redwood oughta do it.

609
00:27:59,965 --> 00:28:02,275
Come on Winslow,
beat it, beat it.

610
00:28:02,310 --> 00:28:03,551
- [Winslow] Oh, all right.

611
00:28:03,586 --> 00:28:06,068
You don't have to be
so cranky about it.

612
00:28:08,689 --> 00:28:09,689
I'm leaving.

613
00:28:12,862 --> 00:28:15,172
- [Bob] Hey, you better
hustle your bustle.

614
00:28:15,206 --> 00:28:16,517
Hurry Winslow, hurry.

615
00:28:16,551 --> 00:28:18,620
Hey look, don't walk, run, run.

616
00:28:20,068 --> 00:28:22,655
- [Winslow] I'm running
as fast as I can.

617
00:28:22,689 --> 00:28:24,482
Oh, there's a tree
that will hold me.

618
00:28:24,517 --> 00:28:25,965
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

619
00:28:28,103 --> 00:28:29,896
Higher, higher.

620
00:28:31,931 --> 00:28:36,172
I can't get a whole lot
higher, maybe just a little.

621
00:28:39,206 --> 00:28:40,413
- [Willard] I found him.

622
00:28:40,448 --> 00:28:41,862
Come on down from
there, Winslow.

623
00:28:41,896 --> 00:28:44,310
- [Winslow] Oh no, you
want to have me for dinner.

624
00:28:44,344 --> 00:28:45,344
- [Willard] What?

625
00:28:45,379 --> 00:28:46,172
Dinner?

626
00:28:46,206 --> 00:28:47,344
You?

627
00:28:47,379 --> 00:28:48,517
Where'd you get such an idea?

628
00:28:48,551 --> 00:28:51,379
Wolves don't eat bears,
nobody eats bears.

629
00:28:51,413 --> 00:28:53,620
We came to tell you
about Christmas.

630
00:28:53,655 --> 00:28:54,655
- [Winslow] You did?

631
00:28:54,689 --> 00:28:56,137
- [Willard] Why, sure we did.

632
00:28:56,172 --> 00:28:57,655
We heard what you were doing.

633
00:28:57,689 --> 00:28:59,448
We know what Christmas is.

634
00:28:59,482 --> 00:29:00,448
- [Winslow] You do?

635
00:29:00,482 --> 00:29:01,896
- [Willard] Course we do.

636
00:29:01,931 --> 00:29:04,068
If you weren't such afraid-y
bear, you'd know that.

637
00:29:04,103 --> 00:29:06,965
Now get your fur lined
carcass down out of that tree

638
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:08,275
and I'll tell ya.

639
00:29:08,310 --> 00:29:10,068
- [Winslow] Well, okay.

640
00:29:10,103 --> 00:29:12,310
- [Willard] Come on,
slide down there chubby.

641
00:29:12,344 --> 00:29:14,827
- [Winslow] Gee, I
better go kinda slow.

642
00:29:14,862 --> 00:29:17,103
That bark is rough.

643
00:29:17,137 --> 00:29:19,758
Wait Willard, wait for me.

644
00:29:19,793 --> 00:29:21,068
I do want to know.

645
00:29:21,103 --> 00:29:23,310
Please wait just a minute.

646
00:29:23,344 --> 00:29:26,310
Willard, can you tell
me what Christmas is?

647
00:29:26,344 --> 00:29:27,413
- [Willard] I'm
surprised you got up

648
00:29:27,448 --> 00:29:29,172
just for that in
the first place.

649
00:29:29,206 --> 00:29:32,000
- [Winslow] Well, I wanted
to know what Christmas is.

650
00:29:32,034 --> 00:29:33,655
Can you please tell me now?

651
00:29:33,689 --> 00:29:35,724
- [Willard] Yep, I
sure can, it's easy.

652
00:29:35,758 --> 00:29:37,172
- [Winslow] It is?

653
00:29:37,206 --> 00:29:39,275
- [Willard] Indeed-y,
Christmas is for families,

654
00:29:39,310 --> 00:29:40,689
that's what it is.

655
00:29:40,724 --> 00:29:42,172
It's our favorite time of year

656
00:29:42,206 --> 00:29:44,517
because we get to
spend it together.

657
00:29:44,551 --> 00:29:48,034
Yes siree, beg your britches,
Christmas is for families.

658
00:29:48,068 --> 00:29:50,827
- [Narrator] Winslow looked
and saw the happy wolf family

659
00:29:50,862 --> 00:29:53,206
running and playing
together on Christmas Eve.

660
00:29:53,241 --> 00:29:56,000
He had to admit, they
certainly looked happy.

661
00:29:56,034 --> 00:29:58,965
- [Winslow] Christmas is for
families, that's the answer?

662
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:01,379
- [Willard] Yes sir
bear, fact of the matter.

663
00:30:01,413 --> 00:30:04,931
Christmas is for families and
that's where you ought to be

664
00:30:04,965 --> 00:30:06,103
with your family.

665
00:30:06,137 --> 00:30:08,206
- [Winslow] Gee, why
didn't I think of that?

666
00:30:08,241 --> 00:30:10,448
Are you sure, Willard?

667
00:30:10,482 --> 00:30:12,517
- [Willard] Sure as
shooting, I'm sure.

668
00:30:12,551 --> 00:30:14,896
Ask Digby the Dog over
at the human's house.

669
00:30:14,931 --> 00:30:16,137
He'll tell ya.

670
00:30:16,172 --> 00:30:17,275
Gotta go now.

671
00:30:17,310 --> 00:30:19,517
Come on boys.

672
00:30:22,344 --> 00:30:24,206
- [Narrator] And with that,
Willard and his whole family

673
00:30:24,241 --> 00:30:27,241
ran up the side of the
mountain valley and were gone.

674
00:30:27,275 --> 00:30:30,310
So Winslow decided he'd
do what Willard suggested.

675
00:30:30,344 --> 00:30:33,482
He'd go ask Digby, the English
setter at the human's house.

676
00:30:33,517 --> 00:30:36,413
So many answers to
the same question.

677
00:30:36,448 --> 00:30:38,551
Christmas was different
for everybody.

678
00:30:38,586 --> 00:30:39,965
Oh, it was almost more

679
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:42,448
than Winslow's little
bear brain could handle.

680
00:30:47,689 --> 00:30:49,827
[barking]

681
00:30:51,620 --> 00:30:54,137
Now, as Winslow got close
to the human's house,

682
00:30:54,172 --> 00:30:55,448
he saw his friend Digby

683
00:30:55,482 --> 00:30:58,551
and oh, was Digby
happy to see him.

684
00:31:01,344 --> 00:31:02,862
- [Digby] Winslow, Winslow,

685
00:31:02,896 --> 00:31:05,724
I didn't think I'd
see you until Spring.

686
00:31:05,758 --> 00:31:07,379
Boy, is it good to see you.

687
00:31:07,413 --> 00:31:08,655
Boy oh boy.

688
00:31:08,689 --> 00:31:10,689
- [Narrator] And Winslow
liked seeing Digby too.

689
00:31:10,724 --> 00:31:13,413
They always had so
much fun together.

690
00:31:13,448 --> 00:31:15,551
The two friends
played and played

691
00:31:15,586 --> 00:31:18,034
until Winslow was very tired.

692
00:31:18,068 --> 00:31:21,586
Digby tried to get the
tired bear to keep playing,

693
00:31:21,620 --> 00:31:25,000
but Winslow just wanted to
lie in the snow for a minute

694
00:31:25,034 --> 00:31:26,206
and catch his breath.

695
00:31:27,379 --> 00:31:29,068
- [Digby] Come on,
Winslow, get up.

696
00:31:32,103 --> 00:31:35,241
- [Narrator] So Winslow
stood all the way up.

697
00:31:35,275 --> 00:31:37,344
- [Digby] What are you
doing here, Winslow?

698
00:31:37,379 --> 00:31:40,275
- [Winslow] Digby, I want
to know what Christmas is.

699
00:31:40,310 --> 00:31:41,724
Do you know?

700
00:31:41,758 --> 00:31:43,827
- [Digby] Do I know
what Christmas is?

701
00:31:43,862 --> 00:31:44,965
Sure, I know.

702
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:46,655
Christmas is for kids.

703
00:31:46,689 --> 00:31:49,068
- [Winslow] Kids, that's
what Christmas is?

704
00:31:49,103 --> 00:31:50,655
How do you know?

705
00:31:50,689 --> 00:31:53,000
- [Digby] Because that's what
it is around the human house.

706
00:31:53,034 --> 00:31:54,206
If you don't believe me,

707
00:31:54,241 --> 00:31:56,620
just go down and
ask my little girl.

708
00:31:56,655 --> 00:31:58,724
- [Winslow] You have
your own little girl?

709
00:31:58,758 --> 00:32:01,931
- [Digby] Yep, most dogs
have their own humans.

710
00:32:01,965 --> 00:32:04,931
She's in the house,
go on, ask her.

711
00:32:04,965 --> 00:32:08,620
- [Narrator] Well, Digby was
his friend, so it must be true.

712
00:32:08,655 --> 00:32:11,724
Winslow decided right
there and then, he'd do it.

713
00:32:11,758 --> 00:32:13,206
The house was just
down the hill.

714
00:32:13,241 --> 00:32:15,931
Digby and Winslow
had rested enough,

715
00:32:15,965 --> 00:32:18,103
time to go and ask
Digby's little girl

716
00:32:18,137 --> 00:32:21,000
and that's exactly what he did.

717
00:32:29,241 --> 00:32:30,862
Winslow had never seen anything

718
00:32:30,896 --> 00:32:32,931
like the human's house before.

719
00:32:32,965 --> 00:32:34,896
He was quite interested.

720
00:32:37,827 --> 00:32:40,931
He walked right up to the
front door of the house

721
00:32:40,965 --> 00:32:41,793
and went in.

722
00:32:46,068 --> 00:32:47,931
Meanwhile, Chrissy
heard something,

723
00:32:47,965 --> 00:32:51,620
so she put down The Magic
Storybook and went to look.

724
00:32:51,655 --> 00:32:53,137
What was it?

725
00:32:53,172 --> 00:32:56,758
Inside, Winslow thought that
the house was very wonderful.

726
00:32:56,793 --> 00:33:00,724
It was warm and so beautifully
decorated, and the tree,

727
00:33:00,758 --> 00:33:03,896
why this wasn't like any tree
he'd ever seen in the forest.

728
00:33:03,931 --> 00:33:05,655
It was a very special tree.

729
00:33:05,689 --> 00:33:09,413
It had colored lights and gaily
wrapped presents underneath

730
00:33:09,448 --> 00:33:10,931
and Winslow thought to himself

731
00:33:10,965 --> 00:33:14,068
that this must be
what Christmas was.

732
00:33:14,103 --> 00:33:15,310
Chrissy was so excited,

733
00:33:15,344 --> 00:33:17,448
she hurried downstairs
to see who it was.

734
00:33:17,482 --> 00:33:22,034
It was Winslow, the very bear
she'd been reading about.

735
00:33:22,068 --> 00:33:23,448
How wonderful?

736
00:33:23,482 --> 00:33:24,724
He'd come to see her.

